<li>    Adam Roberts, "From San Francisco to Sarajevo:  The UN and 
the Use of Force," <i>Survival</i>, Vol. 37, No. 4 (Winter 
1995-1996), p. 25.<p>
<li>    U.S. General Accounting Office, "Future Years Defense 
Program:  Optimistic Estimates Lead to Billions in 
Overprogramming," July 29, 1994.<p>
<li>    Stanley Meisler, "France's Chirac Urges Revamped NATO in 
Address to U.S. Congress," <i>The Los Angeles Times</i>, February 
2, 1996, p. A2.<p>
<li>    See Philip Zelikow and Condoleeza Rice, <i>Germany Unified 
and Europe Transformed:  A Study in Statecraft</i> (Cambridge, 
Mass.:  Harvard University Press, 1995).<p>
<li>    Josef Joffe, "Putting Germany Back Together," <i>Foreign 
Affairs</i>, Vol. 75, No. 1 (January/February 1996), pp. 
161-162<p>
<li>See Peter W. Rodman, "Yalta in the Balkans," <i>National 
